author: Richard Castro
text: I have to say that I have the absolute utmost respect for Japanese professionalism. My old co workers would always try and leave work as soon as they could at the end of the day, even if there were things left behind. But no, Scarlet Rushia stayed behind even after all of those drinks and thanked all of the loving support that she received.

author: Richard Castro
text: Nebby Neberson Itâ€™s because japan takes work life very seriously. They have certain formalities and mannerâ€™s when operating at work. Like the bosses and employees with more seniority always leave the office before the newer workers, and having to wait for certain gestures and queues before being able to go to lunch or leave from a meeting. It can lead to situations where someone is taxing themselves too much but it creates a very well organized and productive/respectable work environment. Boosts moral, co worker connections, and over state of mind.
